[[File:Luke_Skywalker_pilot.png|thumb|right|250px|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] wearing a Rebel flight suit]]
'''Rebel flight suits''', also called '''pilot fatigues''', were garments worn by [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilots]] while flying [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]].<ref name="Dagobah Limited">{{CCG|set=Dagobah Limited|cardname=Rebel Flight Suit}}</ref>

[[File:Biggs_reprise_07.png|thumb|left|250px|Luke, [[Garven Dreis/Legends|Garven Dreis]], and [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs Darklighter]] in pilot fatigues]]

They came in several [[Color/Legends|colors]], including orange, green, and beige.<ref name="Return of the Jedi">{{Film|VI}}</ref> The flight suits had a winter vest such as the ones worn on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]].<ref name="The Empire Strikes Back">{{Film|V}}</ref>

Other gear in the flight suit included [[thermal glove]]s, controls for the suit's systems, flares, stow pockets, an emergency transmitter, insulated boots, a [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]], and protective eye lenses.<ref name="Star Wars Kids Sampler Issue">[[Star Wars Kids (1997)|''Star Wars Kids'' (1997)]] Sampler Issue''</ref>

The flight suit included digital technology which could be customized to a particular starfighter; this increased interface efficiency between a craft and a pilot newly assigned to it.<ref name="Dagobah Limited" />

==Behind the scenes==
Rebel flight suits (base layers) were made by Jay Brand Racewear, who are now known as Jays Racewear.

The [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] suit's orange color was chosen to be reminiscent of the "international orange" U.S. Navy flight suits used from 1957 to 1969. The flight helmet was based on an experimental helmet the military didn't use. Among the items added to this base were pistol flares around the knee reminiscent of those worn by the [[Wikipedia:Luftwaffe|Luftwaffe]], and webbing that originally belonged to parachute rigs.<ref name="Star Wars: The Magic of Myth">''[[Star Wars: The Magic of Myth]]''</ref>

